Jenkins is an open-source automation tool with built-in plugins for continuous integration purposes. It is used to build compile and test your project which makes developers work easy to make changes in the project.

Integrating Jenkins and git is very important if your project is on Git and you want to build it on JenkinsPrerequisites for the Integration process are the Jenkins and Git softwares, that can be easily downloaded from their official website: Git and Jenkins.

After installing these two in your system. You have to set the Environment Variable for these two also. For that go to control panel->System and Security->System->Advance Sys.
